00:00:19.800 --> 00:00:27.240
Peter Rabbit and Other Tales by Beatrix Potter, The Tale of the Flopsie Bunnies.

00:00:27.240 --> 00:00:33.240
It is said that the effect of eating too much lettuce is so horrific.

00:00:33.240 --> 00:00:39.880
I have never felt sleepy after eating lettuces, but then I am not a rabbit.

00:00:39.880 --> 00:00:46.400
They certainly had a very so horrific effect upon the Flopsie Bunnies.

00:00:46.400 --> 00:00:51.400
When Benjamin Bunny grew up, he married his cousin Flopsie.

00:00:51.400 --> 00:00:57.600
They had a large family, and they were very impervivant and cheerful.

00:00:57.600 --> 00:01:01.320
I do not remember the separate names of their children.

00:01:01.320 --> 00:01:05.800
They were generally called the Flopsie Bunnies.

00:01:05.800 --> 00:01:13.180
As there was not always quite enough to eat, Benjamin used to borrow cabbages from Flopsie's

00:01:13.180 --> 00:01:17.800
brother, Peter Rabbit, who kept a nursery garden.

00:01:17.800 --> 00:01:23.120
Sometimes, Peter Rabbit had no cabbages to spare.

00:01:23.120 --> 00:01:29.200
When this happened, the Flopsie Bunnies went across the field to a rubbish heap, in the

00:01:29.200 --> 00:01:34.120
ditch outside Mr McGregor's garden.

00:01:34.120 --> 00:01:37.240
Mr McGregor's rubbish heap was a mixture.

00:01:37.240 --> 00:01:44.800
There were jump bolts and paper bags, mountains of chopped grass from the mowing machine,

00:01:44.800 --> 00:01:52.120
which always tasted oily, and some rotten vegetable marrows, and an old bootle to.

00:01:52.120 --> 00:02:02.440
One day, oh joy, there were a quantity of overgrown lettuces, which had shot into flour.

00:02:02.440 --> 00:02:06.680
The Flopsie Bunnies simply stuffed lettuces.

00:02:06.680 --> 00:02:15.240
By degrees, one after another, they were overcome with slumber and lay down in the mown grass.

00:02:15.240 --> 00:02:19.960
Benjamin was not so much overcome as his children.

00:02:19.960 --> 00:02:27.160
Before going to sleep, he was sufficiently wide awake to put a paper bag over his head

00:02:27.160 --> 00:02:30.440
to keep off the flies.

00:02:30.440 --> 00:02:37.840
The little Flopsie Bunnies slept delightfully in the warm sun, from the long beyond the garden

00:02:37.840 --> 00:02:42.400
came the distant clackety sound of the mowing machine.

00:02:42.400 --> 00:02:49.600
The blue bottles buzzed about the wall, and a little old mouse, picked over the rubbish

00:02:49.600 --> 00:02:51.800
among the jump-ups.

00:02:51.800 --> 00:03:00.120
I can tell you her name, she was called Thomasina Titlnice, a wood mouse with a long tail.

00:03:00.120 --> 00:03:05.560
She rustled across the paper bag, and awakened Benjamin Bunny.

00:03:05.560 --> 00:03:12.040
The mouse apologized profusely and said that she knew Peter Rabbit.

00:03:12.040 --> 00:03:18.640
While she and Benjamin were talking close under the wall, they heard a heavy tread above

00:03:18.640 --> 00:03:27.240
their heads, and suddenly Mr. McGregor emptied out a sackful of lawn mowing right up on the

00:03:27.240 --> 00:03:31.080
top of the sleeping Flopsie Bunnies.

00:03:31.080 --> 00:03:37.880
Benjamin shrank down under his paper bag, the mouse hid in a jam pot.

00:03:37.880 --> 00:03:44.360
The little rabbits smiled sweetly in their sleep under the shower of grass.

00:03:44.360 --> 00:03:49.840
They did not awake because the lettuces have been so so horrific.

00:03:49.840 --> 00:03:57.080
They dreamt that their mother Flopsie was tucking them up in a hay bed.

00:03:57.080 --> 00:04:01.600
The McGregor looked down after emptying his sack.

00:04:01.600 --> 00:04:09.640
He saw some funny little brand tips of ears sticking up through the lawn mowing.

00:04:09.640 --> 00:04:13.880
He stared at them for some time.

00:04:13.880 --> 00:04:20.080
Presently a fly settled on one of them, and it moved.

00:04:20.080 --> 00:04:27.800
Mr. McGregor climbed down onto the rubbish heap.

00:04:27.800 --> 00:04:36.040
"One, two, three, four, five, six, little rabbits," said he, as he dropped them into his

00:04:36.040 --> 00:04:37.040
sack.

00:04:37.040 --> 00:04:43.920
The Flopsie Bunnies dreamt that their mother was turning them over in bed.

00:04:43.920 --> 00:04:49.800
They stirred a little in their sleep, but they did not wake up.

00:04:49.800 --> 00:04:54.560
The McGregor tied up the sack, and left it on the wall.

00:04:54.560 --> 00:04:59.280
He went to put away the mowing machine.

00:04:59.280 --> 00:05:07.880
While he was gone, Mrs. Flopsie Bunnie, who had remained at home, came across the field.

00:05:07.880 --> 00:05:15.120
She looked suspiciously at the sack, and wondered where everybody was.

00:05:15.120 --> 00:05:22.160
Then the mice came out of her jam pot, and Benjamin took the paperbag off his head, and

00:05:22.160 --> 00:05:26.880
they told the doleful tale.

00:05:26.880 --> 00:05:29.480
Benjamin and Flopsie were in despair.

00:05:29.480 --> 00:05:32.520
They could not undo the string.

00:05:32.520 --> 00:05:36.360
But Mrs. Tittle mice was a resourceful person.

00:05:36.360 --> 00:05:40.600
She nibbled a hole in the bottom corner of the sack.

00:05:40.600 --> 00:05:45.920
The little rabbits were pulled out, and pinched to wake them.

00:05:45.920 --> 00:05:53.240
Their parents stuffed the empty sack with three rotten vegetable marrows, an old

00:05:53.240 --> 00:05:58.960
blacking brush, and two decayed turnips.

00:05:58.960 --> 00:06:07.440
Then they all hid under a bush, and watched for Mr. McGregor.

00:06:07.440 --> 00:06:12.760
The McGregor came back, and picked up the sack, and carried it off.

00:06:12.760 --> 00:06:17.720
He carried it hanging down, as if it were rather heavy.

00:06:17.720 --> 00:06:23.000
The Flopsie Bunnies followed at a safe distance.

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:32.960
They watched him go into his house, and then they crept up to the window to listen.

00:06:32.960 --> 00:06:39.280
Mr. McGregor threw down the sack on the stone floor, in a way that would have been extremely

00:06:39.280 --> 00:06:46.120
painful to the Flopsie Bunnies, if they had happened to have been inside it.

00:06:46.120 --> 00:06:50.520
They could hear him drag his chair on the flags, and chuckle.

00:06:50.520 --> 00:06:59.640
"One, two, three, four, five, six, little rabbits," said Mr. McGregor.

00:06:59.640 --> 00:07:03.800
"Hi, what's that? What they've been spoiling now?"

00:07:03.800 --> 00:07:15.600
"In quite Mrs. McGregor," "One, two, three, four, five, six, little fat rabbits," repeated

00:07:15.600 --> 00:07:23.800
Mr. McGregor, counting on his fingers, "One, two, three, don't you be silly?

00:07:23.800 --> 00:07:35.120
What do you mean you silly old man? In the sack, one, two, three, four, five, six," replied

00:07:35.120 --> 00:07:42.200
Mr. McGregor. The youngest Flopsie Bunnies got upon the windowsill.

00:07:42.200 --> 00:07:49.640
Mrs. McGregor took hold of the sack, and felt it. She said she could feel six, but they

00:07:49.640 --> 00:07:55.960
must be old rabbits because they were so hard, and all different shapes.

00:07:55.960 --> 00:08:03.480
"Not fit, do we? But the skins will do fine to line my old cloak? Line your old cloak?"

00:08:03.480 --> 00:08:09.240
She said to Mr. McGregor, "I shall sell them and buy myself backy."

00:08:09.240 --> 00:08:14.800
"Rabbit, tobacco!" "I shall skin them and cut off their reds."

00:08:14.800 --> 00:08:22.200
Mrs. McGregor untied the sack, and put her hand inside. When she felt the vegetables,

00:08:22.200 --> 00:08:31.440
she became very, very angry. She said that Mr. McGregor had done it up her purse.

00:08:31.440 --> 00:08:39.360
And Mr. McGregor was very angry, too. One of the rotomaros came flying through the kitchen

00:08:39.360 --> 00:08:46.400
window, and hit the youngest Flopsie Bunny. It was rather hurt.

00:08:46.400 --> 00:08:52.800
Then Benjamin and Flopsie thought that it was time to go home.

00:08:52.800 --> 00:09:00.080
So Mr. McGregor did not get his tobacco. Mrs. McGregor did not get her rabbit skins.

00:09:00.080 --> 00:09:08.480
But next Christmas, Thomasina Titlemys got a present of enough rabbit wool to make herself

00:09:08.480 --> 00:09:15.680
a cloak and a hood, and a handsome muff and a pair of warm mittens.

00:09:15.680 --> 00:09:20.780
End of the tale of the Flopsie Bunnies.
